Post: Title: Split signature function in solidity by example docs
Body: 
Hi everyone I'm studying the signature verification process. I was reading solidity by example docs [here][1] and I've found this code:
```
/// signature methods.
    function splitSignature(bytes memory sig)
        internal
        pure
        returns (uint8 v, bytes32 r, bytes32 s)
    {
        require(sig.length == 65);

        assembly {
            // first 32 bytes, after the length prefix.
            r := mload(add(sig, 32))
            // second 32 bytes.
            s := mload(add(sig, 64))
            // final byte (first byte of the next 32 bytes).
            v := byte(0, mload(add(sig, 96)))
        }

        return (v, r, s);
    }
```
Why does it work? Can someone explain the assembly part? 
Much appreciate it. 
Thanks.

  [1]: https://docs.soliditylang.org/en/v0.8.17/solidity-by-example.html

